headline: ROYAL CARIBBEAN GROUP TO HOLD CONFERENCE CALL ON FIRST QUARTER 2025 EARNINGS
summary: Royal Caribbean Group (NYSE: RCL) has scheduled a conference call for 10:00 a.m. Eastern Time, Tuesday, April 29, 2025, to discuss the company's first quarter 2025 financial results. The call will be simultaneously webcast on the company's investor relations website, rclinvestor.com. A replay of the webcast will remain available at the same website for 30 days following the call.

headline: MS upgrades Carnival, prefers Royal Caribbean amid recession risks, demand drop
summary: Investing.com -- Morgan Stanley flagged the weakest U.S. cruise demand in three years following fresh channel checks, prompting earnings and price target cuts across the sector. The brokerage Carnival (NYSE:CCL) Corp upgrade to "Equal-weight," but the analysts maintained a cautious tone about the sector while expressing a preference for Royal Caribbean (NYSE:RCL) amid rising macroeconomic uncertainty.

headline: CELEBRITY CRUISES' MUCH-LOVED SHIP CELEBRITY APEX® RETURNS TO SOUTHAMPTON FOR 2025 SUMMER SEASON FROM THE UK
summary: Back by popular demand for her second summer season from Southampton, Celebrity Cruises®' award-winning ship, Celebrity Apex® is offering itineraries to stunning destinations in 2025, from Northern Europe to Ibiza and the Canary Islands, including the premium cruise line's first ever Presidents' Cruise sailing in the Norwegian Fjords.
